{
  "local_port": 49340,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What companies and startups use GitHub?",
  "response": "GitHub is one of the most popular platforms for version control, collaboration, and code hosting, widely adopted by companies and startups across various industries. Its versatility and robust feature set make it suitable for organizations of all sizes, from large enterprises to innovative startups. Here's an overview of some notable companies and startups that use GitHub:\n\n### **Large Enterprises**\n\n1. **Microsoft**\n   - **Details**: As the owner of GitHub since 2018, Microsoft extensively uses the platform for both internal and external projects. Many of its open-source projects, including the .NET framework and Visual Studio Code, are hosted on GitHub.\n   \n2. **Google**\n   - **Details**: While Google primarily relies on its internal systems for proprietary projects, many open-source initiatives like Kubernetes and TensorFlow are hosted on GitHub.\n\n3. **Facebook (Meta)**\n   - **Details**: Meta hosts several open-source projects on GitHub, including React, Jest, and GraphQL, facilitating community contributions and collaboration.\n\n4. **Amazon**\n   - **Details**: Amazon Web Services (AWS) maintains a presence on GitHub, hosting tools, SDKs, and open-source projects to support its vast ecosystem.\n\n5. **IBM**\n   - **Details**: IBM utilizes GitHub for numerous open-source projects, especially those related to cloud computing, artificial intelligence, and blockchain.\n\n6. **Apple**\n   - **Details**: Apple hosts some open-source projects on GitHub, such as the Swift programming language, although much of its development remains proprietary.\n\n7. **Tesla**\n   - **Details**: Tesla leverages GitHub for various software development projects, particularly those related to its autonomous driving systems and vehicle software.\n\n### **Mid-Sized Companies and Startups**\n\n1. **Stripe**\n   - **Details**: Stripe uses GitHub to manage its extensive API libraries and developer tools, promoting open-source collaboration and transparency.\n\n2. **Airbnb**\n   - **Details**: Airbnb hosts several open-source projects on GitHub, including tools for design, engineering, and data science.\n\n3. **Shopify**\n   - **Details**: Shopify leverages GitHub for its platform development, contributing to and maintaining numerous open-source tools that support online commerce.\n\n4. **Slack**\n   - **Details**: Slack's development teams use GitHub to manage integrations, APIs, and various open-source initiatives that enhance its communication platform.\n\n5. **Reddit**\n   - **Details**: Reddit maintains open-source projects on GitHub, including libraries and tools that support its large-scale web platform.\n\n6. **Twilio**\n   - **Details**: Twilio uses GitHub to host SDKs, APIs, and developer tools, fostering a collaborative environment for building communication solutions.\n\n7. **Notion**\n   - **Details**: Notion leverages GitHub for parts of its development workflow, particularly for integrations and community-driven enhancements.\n\n### **Tech Startups and Innovators**\n\n1. **HashiCorp**\n   - **Details**: Specializing in infrastructure automation, HashiCorp hosts flagship projects like Terraform, Vault, and Consul on GitHub, encouraging community contributions.\n\n2. **GitLab**\n   - **Details**: Although a competitor in the DevOps space, GitLab utilizes GitHub for certain open-source components and community interactions.\n\n3. **Twilio**\n   - **Details**: Twilio\u2019s APIs and developer tools are managed on GitHub, enabling developers to build and integrate communication solutions seamlessly.\n\n4. **Datadog**\n   - **Details**: Datadog uses GitHub to manage integrations, agents, and various monitoring tools that support its cloud infrastructure monitoring services.\n\n5. **Elastic**\n   - **Details**: The company behind Elasticsearch and the Elastic Stack hosts its projects on GitHub, facilitating widespread adoption and collaboration.\n\n### **Non-Tech Companies Using GitHub**\n\n1. **NASA**\n   - **Details**: NASA hosts several projects on GitHub, including data repositories, mission tools, and educational resources, promoting transparency and collaboration.\n\n2. **The U.S. Government**\n   - **Details**: Various government agencies use GitHub to share open data, software tools, and collaborative projects with the public.\n\n3. **Spotify**\n   - **Details**: Spotify maintains open-source projects related to music data processing, APIs, and developer tools on GitHub.\n\n### **Why Companies Choose GitHub**\n\n- **Collaboration**: GitHub offers robust tools for collaboration, including pull requests, code reviews, and issue tracking, which streamline the development process.\n- **Integration**: With a vast ecosystem of integrations and APIs, GitHub seamlessly connects with numerous services and tools used in software development.\n- **Community Engagement**: Hosting projects on GitHub allows companies to engage with the open-source community, fostering innovation and external contributions.\n- **Security**: GitHub provides advanced security features, such as vulnerability scanning and dependency management, ensuring code integrity and safety.\n- **Scalability**: Whether managing small projects or large, complex codebases, GitHub scales to meet the needs of diverse organizations.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nGitHub's widespread adoption across various sectors underscores its significance in the modern software development landscape. From tech giants like Microsoft and Google to innovative startups and even non-tech organizations, GitHub serves as a pivotal platform for collaboration, open-source development, and efficient code management. Whether you're a developer, a company looking to streamline your development workflow, or someone interested in contributing to open-source projects, GitHub offers the tools and community to support your goals.",
